      answer: 'Digital printable products typically receive reviews from 1% to 5% of buyers, with most sellers experiencing rates in the 2% to 3% range. This is lower than physical product review rates because digital products lack the tangible presence that reminds buyers to evaluate their purchase. Implementing professional thank-you inserts, well-timed follow-up messages, and consistent review responses can improve your rate toward the upper end of this range, but expecting every buyer to leave a review is unrealistic. Focus on maximizing the total number of transactions through catalog growth and product quality rather than trying to dramatically increase the per-transaction review rate. A 3% review rate on 1,000 annual sales produces 30 reviews, which provides substantial social proof across your catalog.',
